The paper focuses on visual navigation using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of regularization techniques and the incorporation of information theory suggest a focus on optimization and control (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the experiments conducted on the AI2-THOR framework and the Active Vision Dataset (AVD) suggest a focus on robotics (cs.SY).
